Here is my Kanban, which documents my developing plans of each week, the goal of each week, and what is the progress now.
I try to break every function into small user stories and try to realize them in a smooth pace. This Kanban could help you to track my developing progress and decide if my developing progress is smooth and steady enough.
Many code tests and function tests would also appear in the Kanban because I don't wish my game get crashed finally when everything is finished.
In this course, I adopt agile practice as the working style instead of waterfall.
This documentation could also be used as an evidence of professionalism.
